{
  "stem": "20142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't ask many questions, they didn't hit anybody or anything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Aleja ?] Szucha, spelled S-Z-U-C-H-A, was a former ministry of education and the cultural affairs and religious affairs of the Polish government that was converted by the Gestapo headquarters-- to the Gestapo headquarter in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For the Warsaw--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't ask questions.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They-- they just took me, they brought me in and during the interrogation they asked for names that I never heard, that I couldn't deliver them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because the beating was outstanding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I have a scar on my face from the-- from the accident, I had worse scars before being beaten up.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had my share of beating by the interrogators in the war-- in the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember quite well the names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a main interrogator, [GERMAN] Staff Sergeant Schilling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A huge man, obese man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] whenever he hit someone-- and he hit me a good number of times-- I-- I felt it quite well.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was-- must have been bouncing like a ball when he was hitting me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, of course, he would lose-- as many times as they hit you, that you'd lose your consciousness.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I woke up in that cellar in the compound, and they had then Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And whatever saved me was the dampness of this compound, that it was cold and watery.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I held my hands, of course, against the floor, and then put it on my face and I came to myself.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And somehow I was surviving and transported back to Pawiak and to this [? later ?] again brought the [INAUDIBLE] Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was going on like this for two months until--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They was constantly asking about names that I never heard.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
